{"entity":{"id":"reclw5MqDa0cwvCoU","type":"chapter","slug":"reclw5MqDa0cwvCoU","label":"Job.11","rawId":"reclw5MqDa0cwvCoU","book":{"id":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","type":"book","slug":"job","label":"Job","subtitle":"Poetry-Wisdom","count":1070,"description":"42 chapters, 190 people, 6 places"}},"stats":{"verses":20,"people":2,"places":0,"events":1},"nodes":[{"id":"reclw5MqDa0cwvCoU","type":"chapter","group":"focus","label":"Job.11","slug":"job_11","score":20},{"id":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","type":"book","group":"book","label":"Job","slug":"job","score":1070},{"id":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"God","slug":"god_1324","score":3},{"id":"reczamkTBkamDRCDW","type":"person","group":"mentioned","label":"Zophar","slug":"zophar_3105","score":1},{"id":"recMNT9RB1RJiLlYW","type":"event","group":"event","label":"Job's Trial","slug":"event-117","score":20}],"links":[{"source":"reclw5MqDa0cwvCoU","target":"recOA8nVVhKs30PSI","label":"part of"},{"source":"reclw5MqDa0cwvCoU","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reclw5MqDa0cwvCoU","target":"reczamkTBkamDRCDW","label":"mentions"},{"source":"reclw5MqDa0cwvCoU","target":"recMNT9RB1RJiLlYW","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recLMaqZLZhuOVbtr","ref":"Job.11.1","text":"Then answered Zophar the Naamathite, and said,","year":-1520},{"id":"recrL4q8B2BAY6nb6","ref":"Job.11.2","text":"Should not the multitude of words be answered? and should a man full of talk be justified?","year":-1520},{"id":"recA8jdeAPG0iKR3n","ref":"Job.11.3","text":"Should thy lies make men hold their peace? and when thou mockest, shall no man make thee ashamed?","year":-1520},{"id":"rec8QC8EMxUiTbEmH","ref":"Job.11.4","text":"For thou hast said, My doctrine is pure, and I am clean in thine eyes.","year":-1520},{"id":"recARtpDITn4NPIhL","ref":"Job.11.5","text":"But oh that God would speak, and open his lips against thee;","year":-1520},{"id":"reck2rPKls0gdjCyh","ref":"Job.11.6","text":"And that he would shew thee the secrets of wisdom, that they are double to that which is! Know therefore that God exacteth of thee less than thine iniquity deserveth.","year":-1520},{"id":"recbmDMRR8MSdcbPI","ref":"Job.11.7","text":"Canst thou by searching find out God? canst thou find out the Almighty unto perfection?","year":-1520},{"id":"recP4OerNfcVcYqsc","ref":"Job.11.8","text":"It is as high as heaven; what canst thou do? deeper than hell; what canst thou know?","year":-1520}]}
